// PositioningText.astro
// The missing primitive — bounded disclosure between agent delegates
---

<section class="section reveal" id="positioning">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="positioning">
      <p>
        Agent coordination today is either <strong>shallow</strong> — public APIs, no
        confidentiality — or <strong>opaque</strong>, routed through intermediaries with
        no verifiable record of what was disclosed.
      </p>
      <p>
        The missing primitive is <strong>bounded disclosure</strong>: a mechanism where
        two agents exchange a constrained, schema-validated signal under a jointly
        consented contract, producing a receipt that proves exactly what occurred.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

